    <h2>Arguments</h2>
    <dl>
      <dt>breaks</dt>
      <dd>A vector of breaks, a function that given
  the scale limits returns a vector of breaks, or a
  character vector, specifying the width between breaks.
  For more information about the first two, see
  <code><a href='continuous_scale.html'>continuous_scale</a></code>, for more information
  about the last, see <code><a href='http://www.inside-r.org/r-doc/scales/date_breaks'>date_breaks</a></code>`.</dd>
      <dt>minor_breaks</dt>
      <dd>Either <code>NULL</code> for no minor
  breaks, <code>waiver()</code> for the default breaks (one minor
  break between each major break), a numeric vector of
  positions, or a function that given the limits returns a
  vector of minor breaks.</dd>
      <dt>...</dt>
      <dd>common continuous scale parameters:
  <code>name</code>, <code>breaks</code>, <code>labels</code>,
  <code>na.value</code>, <code>limits</code> and <code>trans</code>.  See
  <code><a href='continuous_scale.html'>continuous_scale</a></code> for more details</dd>
      <dt>expand</dt>
      <dd>a numeric vector of length two giving
  multiplicative and additive expansion constants. These
  constants ensure that the data is placed some distance
  away from the axes.</dd>
    </dl>
    
